<paragraph blockId="0.[747,1397,1345,1952]" box="[747,1249,1345,1369]" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[747,1249,1345,1369]" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">
1. Three vicariant species of section 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Balkwill &amp; Balkwill" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1157,1249,1345,1369]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1157,1249,1345,1369]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">Barleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[747,1397,1345,1952]" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">
– The Katangan novelty 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[886,1006,1376,1400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis box="[886,1006,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related, morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. B. Clarke (Clarke" authorityYear="1900" box="[921,1057,1407,1430]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyasensis">
<emphasis box="[921,1057,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. nyasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1117,1251,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. sunzuana</emphasis>
which differ mainly by the well developed upper lobes of their corolla, upper lobes which are lacking or extremely reduced in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The other differences include spiny bracteoles (‘interpetiolar spines’ of various authors), calyx lobe margins provided with straight stiff-tipped teeth in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. B. Clarke (Clarke" authorityYear="1900" box="[1099,1231,1561,1584]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyasensis">
<emphasis box="[1099,1231,1561,1584]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. nyasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. sunzuana</emphasis>
whereas soft bracteoles and upwards-curved soft-tipped teeth characterize the calyx lobe margins in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[1224,1341,1621,1645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis box="[1224,1341,1621,1645]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The ecology and altitude ranges seem also to be different, as indicated below after the lists of the collected specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. B. Clarke (Clarke" authorityYear="1900" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyasensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. nyasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[901,1032,1714,1737]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. sunzuana</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[747,1397,1345,1952]" lastBlockId="1.[55,704,647,700]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. B. Clarke (Clarke" authorityYear="1900" box="[785,919,1745,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyasensis">
<emphasis box="[785,919,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. nyasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[975,1108,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. sunzuana</emphasis>
were put in sect. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Balkwill &amp; Balkwill" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1306,1396,1744,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1306,1396,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">Barleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[782,1085,1774,1799]" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" refId="ref9206" refString="Balkwill M. - J., Balkwill K. (1997) Delimitation and infrageneric classification of Barleria (Acanthaceae). Kew Bulletin 52: 535 - 573. [available at http: // www. jstor. org / pss / 4110286]" type="journal article">Balkwill &amp; Balkwill (1997)</bibRefCitation>
; this section is characterized by simple axillary inflorescences, toothed calyx lobes, corolla lobes in a 2 + 3 configuration, and two fertile stamens with three staminodes. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[995,1111,1867,1891]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis box="[995,1111,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be placed without any doubt in the same section. Another species of that section, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. bremekampii</emphasis>
Oberm., although morphologically distant from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[55,173,647,671]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis box="[55,173,647,671]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="83">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has also extremely reduced upper corolla lobes (see drawing in 
<bibRefCitation box="[226,508,676,700]" pageId="1" pageNumber="83" refId="ref9206" refString="Balkwill M. - J., Balkwill K. (1997) Delimitation and infrageneric classification of Barleria (Acanthaceae). Kew Bulletin 52: 535 - 573. [available at http: // www. jstor. org / pss / 4110286]" type="journal article">Balkwill &amp; Balkwill 1997</bibRefCitation>
: 556, B1).
</paragraph>
